    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="545"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1551a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 3, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>281. Papers today carry following article by William Hillman, Universal Service
                    correspondent: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Britain today offered France a military alliance to safeguard France’s
                            German frontier against ‘all attacks’ in exchange for French support of
                            League of Nations sanctions against Italy and use of Toulon, Manse [<hi
                                rend="italic">sic</hi>], as a Mediterranean naval base for the
                            British fleet.</p>
                        <p>“This momentous proposal to the French Government, which long has
                            demanded British guarantees of French security against Germany, was
                            agreed to by the British cabinet in full session at 10 Downing Street
                            even as Mussolini mobilized the Italian nation to signalize the crossing
                            of Italian armies from Eritrea into the African no man’s land fringing
                            Ethiopia.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Department wishes any information you have concerning this news.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
